main event: Several bright stationary or tumbling silver or translucent objects were observed on February 23, 1954.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 7 minutes,The objects were at an elevation of about 30 degrees,There were multiple parts to the report detailing the characteristics and trajectory of the objects,The sighting included radar reports confirming the observation,The observer could not close in on the objects as they scrambled a military aircraft.
sighted object: bright stationary or tumbling silver or translucent objects
witness description: USAF personnel observing from Nellis AFB
